Harold S. Bucquet https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harold_S._Bucquet 0 Harold S. Bucquet (10 April 1891 – 13 February 1946) was an English film director. He directed 26 films between 1936 and 1945. His 1937 film Torture Money won an Academy Award for the Best Short Subject (Two-Reel).He was born in London, England and died in Los Angeles, California. He is interred at Glendale's Forest Lawn Memorial Park Cemetery. Harold_S._Bucquet ( 10_April_1891 – 13_February_1946 ) was an_English_film_director . He directed 26_films between 1936_and_1945 .
